text: Abdul Hamid Mahmud (January 15, 1942 â€“ January 31, 2021) was an Indonesian politician. He was Regent of Malang from 1985 to 1990 and 1990 to 1995. He also was Deputy Governor of East Java for Government and Welfare from 1995 to 2000. Mahmud died on January 31, 2021 at a hospital in Malang from heart disease, aged 79. ==References== Category:Indonesian politicians Category:1942 births Category:2021 deaths Category:Disease-related deaths in Indonesia Category:Deaths from heart disease
